14 WHEREAS, dedicated individuals in Oklahoma breed dogs to develop
15 unique predictable characteristics that enable dogs to excel in a
16 wide range of beneficial areas; and
17 WHEREAS, purebred dogs are living legacies of the cultures that
18 created them, and historically, these dogs worked alongside their
19 people and provided them companionship; and
20 WHEREAS, the service of these breeds continues as they work
21 alongside humans and provide inestimable companionship as guide
22 dogs, service dogs, conservation dogs, livestock guardians, search
23 and rescue dogs, earth dogs, police dogs, canine soldiers serving by
